glosses: to be cold, feel cold; to feel a chill
to get a chill, catch a chill

etymology:
From Ottoman Turkish اوشومك (üşümek, “to feel cold, shiver with cold”), from Proto-Turkic *üli-, *üĺi- (“to freeze, congeal”).
Cognates
Cognate with Old Turkic [script needed] (üşi-, “to feel cold”), Azerbaijani üşümək (“to shiver, be cold”), Bashkir өшөү (öşöw, “to feel cold”), Kazakh үсу (üsu, “to freeze”), Kyrgyz үшүү (üşüü, “to feel cold”), Southern Altai ӱжӱӱр (üžüür), Turkmen üşemek (“to be cold”), Tuvan үжүүр (üjüür, “to grow numb”), Yakut үлүй (ülüy, “to be frostbitten”).
